From robinson Michael Robinson Subject Re Need advice for riding with someone on pillion In article Pat Loughery writes Also remember that it's much more draining and tiring to ride up than by yourself because you're concentrating on much more and in the Zen of the moment Remember The first few times I pillioned someone whose safety was a great concern to me as opposed to brothers I almost got us both killed on several I was surprised to discover that it is much safer to just drive than to distract yourself by trying to be unusually cautious and Abruptly adopting a novel set of thought patterns and riding strategies while piloting a bike is just asking for Michael Robinson UUCP ucbvax cogsci robinson INTERNET